# ci-coverage-threshold-single-source - History

## v2.0.0 (2026-03-25)

**Changed by:** Issue #1511, PR #1554 - raise combined coverage floor from 9% to 75%
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Extended skill to cover removing --cov-fail-under from pyproject.toml addopts (not just CI)
- Added dual-threshold design pattern (combined floor + per-step CI floors)
- Added guidance on updating consistency check scripts that validate addopts
- Added pixi run test-unit local task pattern for CI parity
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts entries

### Why
v1.0.0 only covered removing --cov-fail-under from CI workflows.
Issue #1511 revealed --cov-fail-under=9 in addopts was redundant with fail_under=9,
and the 9% floor was cosmetically low. The fix removed the addopts flag and raised
fail_under to 75%.

### Previous version (v1.0.0) snapshot

Single source of truth skill covering CI workflow --cov-fail-under removal.
Issue #754, PR #868. Threshold removed: --cov-fail-under=72. Authoritative: fail_under=73.

